overview:
Kyle Jenke is in business development and a member of the leadership team at EdeniQ, Inc based in Mountain View, CA.

Prior to EdeniQ, Mr. Jenke was in the Energy Group at Goldman Sachs in New York City where he led investments in the global energy industry with a particular focus on the emerging oil & gas markets such as West Africa, Brazil, and Asia. Mr. Jenke also relocated to India in 2010 to lead the development of Goldman’s India Energy Group.

Kyle Jenke attended the University of Richmond in Virginia where he graduated with honors and was awarded the Robins School of Business Alumni Scholarship and William L. Phillips Scholar Award. Mr. Jenke received his degree in Business Administration with a triple concentration in Finance, Marketing, and International Business.

A 4th generation San Francisco Bay Area native, Kyle Jenke grew up in Los Altos before moving with his family to Hong Kong for 4 years.
